[{"location":"sliding_window/#Sliding-window-functions","page":"Sliding window","title":"Sliding window functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"sliding_window/","page":"Sliding window","title":"Sliding window","text":"sliding_window","category":"page"},{"location":"sliding_window/#Heine.sliding_window","page":"Sliding window","title":"Heine.sliding_window","text":"sliding_window(x::AbstractVector{X}, y::AbstractVector{Y};\n    f::Function, \n    width::Int, \n    step::Int\n    ) where {X, Y <: Real}\n\nCalculates the function f::Function for input-vectors x::AbstractVector and  y::AbstractVector in a \"sliding window\" of constant width::Int and  jumps with step::Int.\n\nReturns two vectors containing the calculated values.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> using Heine, Statistics\njulia> sliding_window([1,2,3,4,5,6], [1,3,4,5,7,8], f = mean, width = 3, step = 3)\n([2, 5], [2.6666666666666665, 6.666666666666667])\njulia> sliding_window([1,2,3,4,5,6], [1,3,4,5,7,8], f = median, width = 3, step = 3)\n([2, 5], [3.0, 7.0])\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = Heine","category":"page"},{"location":"#Heine","page":"Home","title":"Heine","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for Heine.","category":"page"}]
